# Flutter Architecture Rules

## Folder structure

```
lib/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core/           # App-wide infrastructure (theme, router, config, network, utils)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ features/       # One directory per vertical slice
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>/
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data/         # Repositories impl, API clients, local DAO adapters
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ domain/       # Entities, abstract repositories, use-cases
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ presentation/ # Screens, widgets, Riverpod providers
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ shared/         # Reusable widgets and models used by 2+ features
```

## Layer rules

- `presentation/` imports `domain/` only ‚Äî never another feature's `data/`.
- `data/` implements `domain/` interfaces ‚Äî never imports `presentation/`.
- Cross-feature sharing goes through `core/` or `shared/`, never feature‚Üífeature.
- `core/` has no dependency on any feature.

## Naming conventions

| Type | Naming | File |
|------|--------|------|
| Screen | `FooScreen` | `foo_screen.dart` |
| Widget | `FooCard`, `FooButton` | `foo_card.dart` |
| Provider | `fooProvider` | `foo_provider.dart` or `foo_providers.dart` |
| Repository (abstract) | `FooRepository` | `foo_repository.dart` |
| Repository (impl) | `FooRepositoryImpl` | `foo_repository_impl.dart` |
| Entity | `Foo` (Freezed) | `foo.dart` |
| Use-case | `GetFooUseCase` | `get_foo_use_case.dart` |

## Adding a new feature checklist

1. Create `lib/features/<name>/{data,domain,presentation}/` directories.
2. Define entity in `domain/entities/`.
3. Define repository interface in `domain/repositories/`.
4. Implement repository in `data/repositories/`.
5. Create Riverpod provider in `presentation/providers/`.
6. Build screen in `presentation/<name>_screen.dart`.
7. Register route in `core/router/app_router.dart`.

## What NOT to do

- Don't put business logic inside a widget's `build()`.
- Don't hardcode strings or colors ‚Äî use `AppColors`, `AppTypography`, localization keys.
- Don't navigate with `Navigator.push` ‚Äî use `context.go()` from go_router.
- Don't call APIs directly from presentation ‚Äî always go through a repository.
